# ThreadSeeker frontend — environment variables
#
# The backend now ships as Cloudflare Pages Functions alongside the frontend,
# so in production `/api/*` is same-origin and no env vars are required.
#
# For local dev without `wrangler pages dev`, set this to "disabled" to skip
# the Pages-Function-backed sources (everything direct-CORS still works). To
# point at a local Wrangler instance, set it to e.g. http://localhost:8788.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=disabled
NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=

# --- Server-side Pages Function secrets (NOT shipped to the browser) ---
# Optional. The /api/gh function adds this as a Bearer token to GitHub API
# calls, lifting GitHub from the unauthenticated 10 req/min (search) / 60
# req/hr (core) shared limit to 30 req/min / 5000 req/hr. Everything works
# without it (just unauthenticated). In production set it as a Pages secret;
# for `wrangler pages dev`, put it in a git-ignored .dev.vars file.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxx   (a fine-grained PAT with public-repo read is plenty)
#
# Optional. Unlocks the AI layer (/api/optimize-queries + /api/synthesize):
# query understanding for long queries + a cross-source verdict above results.
# Free tier at console.groq.com. Without it, the deterministic engine is the
# baseline and no AI renders. Edge-cached.
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_xxx
